<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,704,942]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,267,775,797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis:—</emphasis>
This species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Praeger 1921: 13) A. Berger (1930: 462)" authorityName="A. Berger" authorityPageNumber="462" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Praeger" baseAuthorityPageNumber="13" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[623,1143,776,798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sinocrassula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis box="[623,733,776,797]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">S. ambigua</emphasis>
(Praeger 1921:13) A. Berger (1930: 462)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having turquoise leaves and the tip of the leaves red (
<figureCitation box="[543,684,812,834]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,211,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,190,1981]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocrassula jiaozishanensis.—A. Habit.—B. Inflorescence.—C. Infructescence.—D, E. Leaf.—F, G. Bract.—H, I, J, K, L, M. Flowers.—N. Ovary.—O. Flower structure. Photographed by C. Chen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6375102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6375102/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Fig. 1 A, D, E</figureCitation>
) (vs. beige to purplish-red leaves and the tip no colour change in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Berger" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Praeger" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[1328,1437,812,833]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sinocrassula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis box="[1328,1437,812,833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">S. ambigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), length of sepals and perianth segments subequal (
<figureCitation box="[691,827,848,870]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,211,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,190,1981]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocrassula jiaozishanensis.—A. Habit.—B. Inflorescence.—C. Infructescence.—D, E. Leaf.—F, G. Bract.—H, I, J, K, L, M. Flowers.—N. Ovary.—O. Flower structure. Photographed by C. Chen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6375102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6375102/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Fig. 1 H, I, J</figureCitation>
) (vs. sepals significantly longer than perianth in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Berger" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Praeger" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[1326,1437,848,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sinocrassula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis box="[1326,1437,848,869]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">S. ambigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), inflorescence 
<quantity box="[323,418,884,905]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="15.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="10.0">10–20 cm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[431,510,884,906]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,211,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,190,1981]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocrassula jiaozishanensis.—A. Habit.—B. Inflorescence.—C. Infructescence.—D, E. Leaf.—F, G. Bract.—H, I, J, K, L, M. Flowers.—N. Ovary.—O. Flower structure. Photographed by C. Chen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6375102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6375102/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Fig. 1 A</figureCitation>
) (vs. 
<quantity box="[565,671,884,906]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="1.85" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–2.5 cm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Berger" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Praeger" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[702,810,884,905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sinocrassula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis box="[702,810,884,905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">S. ambigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), nectar scale oblong 0.3 × 
<quantity box="[1075,1148,884,906]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
(vs. 0.5 × 
<quantity box="[1250,1326,884,906]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, subquadrate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Berger" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Praeger" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[214,322,920,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sinocrassula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis box="[214,322,920,941]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">S. ambigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,988,1699]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,381,988,1014]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">
Description (
<figureCitation box="[292,364,988,1014]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,211,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,190,1981]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocrassula jiaozishanensis.—A. Habit.—B. Inflorescence.—C. Infructescence.—D, E. Leaf.—F, G. Bract.—H, I, J, K, L, M. Flowers.—N. Ovary.—O. Flower structure. Photographed by C. Chen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6375102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6375102/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Perennial, glabrous, succulent. Roots fibrous. Stems creeping, erect or somewhat pendulous, terete. Basal leaves opposite, not rosulate, stem leaves alternate, round obovate or oblanceolate to oblong, acute or cuspidate, turquoise with red apex, 2–3.5 × 
<quantity box="[648,759,1060,1087]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="1.65" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.3">1.3–2 cm</quantity>
. Flowering stems terminal, erect, apex bending or drooping ca. 
<quantity box="[176,289,1096,1123]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="15.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="10.0">10–20 cm</quantity>
tall; inflorescences corymbiform, ca. 20–45-flowered cyme to 
<quantity box="[1009,1080,1096,1123]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
in diam; bracts sessile, alternate or opposite, obovate or lanceolate, 0.15–1.5 × 
<quantity box="[683,816,1132,1159]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="0.44999999999999996" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.7 cm</quantity>
. Flowers bisexual, ca. 
<quantity box="[1085,1154,1132,1159]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
in diam; sepals narrowly triangular, ca. 3.5 × 
<quantity box="[358,446,1168,1195]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
, minutely papillate; petals base white, central and above rose to purple, oblong-lanceolate, apex cuspidate, ca. 1.8 × 
<quantity box="[429,520,1204,1231]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
; stamens ca. 
<quantity box="[674,735,1204,1230]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="4.0">4mm</quantity>
; anthers purple, orbicular, pollen yellow. Nectar scales yellow, oblong or kidney-shaped, 0.55–0.65 × 
<quantity box="[564,715,1240,1267]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.275" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.25">0.25–0.3 mm</quantity>
. Carpels 5, distinct, ovate-lanceolate. ca. 
<quantity box="[1171,1238,1240,1267]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
. Styles erect, short, ca. 
<quantity box="[175,263,1276,1303]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
, apex red. Fl. Mar-May, fr. Apr-Jun.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,988,1699]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">
