<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,988,1699]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,494,1384,1410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Distribution and Habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chao Chen, J. G. Wang &amp; Z. R. He" authorityYear="2022" box="[522,844,1384,1410]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sinocrassula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jiaozishanensis">
<emphasis box="[522,844,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Sinocrassula jiaozishanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from Jiduo village, Xueshan Township, Luquan County, in the crevice of cliffs with epilithic plants (e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hook. et Grev.) Maxim" authorityName="Maxim" baseAuthorityName="Hook. et Grev." box="[909,1447,1420,1447]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Selaginellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulvinata">
<emphasis box="[909,1152,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Selaginella pulvinata</emphasis>
(Hook. et Grev.) Maxim
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Royle) Royle" authorityName="Royle" baseAuthorityName="Royle" box="[136,509,1456,1483]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Incarvillea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arguta">
<emphasis box="[136,340,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Incarvillea arguta</emphasis>
(Royle) Royle
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Roxb.) Hochst var. lanceolatus" box="[520,1135,1456,1483]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arthraxon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lanceolatus" variety="lanceolatus">
<emphasis box="[520,771,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Arthraxon lanceolatus</emphasis>
(Roxb.) Hochst var. 
<emphasis box="[1006,1135,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">lanceolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1229,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1927,1949]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,208,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-31@5.[151,1436,190,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Field information of Sinocrassula jiaozishanensis.—A. Seedling.—B. Mature plant.—C, D. Population.—E. Habitat. Photographed by C. Chen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6375108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6375108/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,988,1699]" box="[189,950,1492,1518]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,1492,1518]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Flowering time March-May, fruiting time April-June.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,988,1699]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,438,1528,1554]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Conservation status:</emphasis>
In the 
<typeStatus box="[524,572,1529,1555]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<emphasis box="[708,1040,1528,1554]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chao Chen, J. G. Wang &amp; Z. R. He" authorityYear="2022" box="[708,1036,1528,1554]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sinocrassula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jiaozishanensis">Sinocrassula jiaozishanensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
only 10 plants were found, and we failed to find more populations or individuals besides 
<typeStatus box="[770,818,1565,1591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
locality. Because of the restricted distribution and the peculiar habitat, we assessed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chao Chen, J. G. Wang &amp; Z. R. He" authorityYear="2022" box="[465,664,1600,1626]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sinocrassula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jiaozishanensis">
<emphasis box="[465,664,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">S. jiaozishanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as Critically Endangered (CR) according to criterion D (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[1301,1439,1600,1626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13" refId="ref3158" refString="IUCN (2017) The IUCN red list of threatened species, version 2017. 1. IUCN Red List Unit. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / (accessed 10 April 2017)" type="url" year="2017">IUCN 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,988,1699]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1636,1662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet “ 
<emphasis box="[594,782,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">jiaozishanensis”</emphasis>
refers to Jiaozi mountain where the species was discovered. Jiaozi Mountain is a famous mountain in Kunming, 
<collectingRegion box="[719,914,1672,1699]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="3" pageNumber="13">Yunnan province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
